roduction company or the news/article you have been put as sourced. If the film release date has not been announced, indicate or put it as \"TBA\" shortened for \"To be announced\".\n\n\u2022 EVERYTHING YOU HAVE BEEN CONTRIBUTED HERE WILL REFLECT TO THE PERSON WHO SEARCHES, VIEWS, VISITS, AND CHECKS THE ARTICLES FROM ALL OVER THE WORLD. IT IS IMPORTANT THAT WE CONTRIBUTE RELIABLY SO THAT WE CAN PROMOTE OUR OWN ENTERTAINMENT INDUSTRY.\n\n\u2022 THIS NOTE IS APPLICABLE TO THE ARTICLES OF FILM PRODUCTION OF THE PHILIPPINES HERE IN WIKIPEDIA\u2013BOTH ENGLISH AND TAGALOG.\n\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\n;Color key\n{{plainlist|\n* {{Color box|#FFFACD|border=darkgray}} \u2013 a foreign film distributed by Viva International Pictures\n* {{Color box|#FFFFFF|border=darkgray}} \u2013 Film(s) that are not colored/white colored are regular release in the cinemas and is not an entry to any film festival inside or outside the country.\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! style=\"width:30%;\"| Film <!--ALWAYS PUT IT IN ORDER OF THE RELEASE DATE-->\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Release\n! style=\"width:60%;\"| Notes\n|-\n|-\n|''[[Pedro Penduko (film)|Pedro Penduko]]''\n| 2020\n| co-production with Epik Studios<ref>[http://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/10/17/its-confirmed-james-reid-is-the-new-pedro-penduko It's confirmed: James Reid is the new Pedro Penduko]. ''ABS-CBN News''. Published on 2017-08-10. Retrieved 2017-08-11.</ref>\n|-\n|''Osyana''\n|2020\n|co-production with Epik Studios\n|-\n|''Delta''\n|TBA\n|\n|-\n| ''The Nurse''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://push.abs-cbn.com/2017/10/7/fresh-scoops/watch-nadine-lustre-reveals-her-future-projects-169524|title=Nadine Lustre reveals her future projects|publisher=[[ABS-CBN]]|website=PUSH|date=October 7, 2017|time=10:58 AM|author=Leary, Joan|accessdate=January 31, 2018}}</ref>\n| TBA\n| co-production with The IdeaFirst Company<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.inquirer.net/238965/nadine-lustre-is-solo-star-in-horror-movie-the-nurse|title=Nadine Lustre is solo star in horror movie \u2018The Nurse\u2019|publisher=Inquirer News|website=Inquirer|date=August 18, 2017|time=01:17 PM|author=Abanilla, Clarizel|accessdate=January 31, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Sana All''<ref>https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=htPxixZuhLo</ref>\n| TBA\n|\n|-\n| ''Love The Way U Lie'' <ref>https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=X8TH38WFi2s</ref>\n| TBA\n|\n|-\n| '' A Hard Day''<ref>https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=uw9jkEYlr3s</ref>\n| TBA\n|\n|-\n| ''SpellBound''\n| TBA\n|\n|-\n|''Mang Jose''\n|TBA\n|\n|-\n|''Rooftop''\n|TBA\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.imdb.com/company/co0046157/ List of Viva Films Movies at IMDB.Com]\n\n{{Viva Communications}}\n{{Philippine production companies and film studios}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Films produced and released by Viva Films}}\n[[Category:Viva Films| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of Philippine films|Viva Films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\nThis is a list of feature-length theatrical films produced and released by the Filipino motion picture company '''''[[Viva Films]]''''' since its foundation in 1981.\n\n{{Expand list|type=Film|date=March 2018}}\n{{horizontal TOC|nonum=yes}}\n\n==2013==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! style=\"width:30%;\"| Film <!--ALWAYS PUT IT IN ORDER OF THE RELEASE DATE-->\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Release\n! style=\"width:60%;\"| Notes\n|-\n| ''Menor de Edad''\n| January 23\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Fighting Chefs]]''\n| March 6\n| co-production with Rockets Productions\n|-\n| ''[[It Takes a Man and a Woman]]''\n| March 30\n| co-production with [[Star Cinema]]\n|-\n| ''Ang Huling Henya''\n| August 21\n| co-production with MVP Pictures\n|-\n| ''[[Momzillas]]''\n| September 18\n| co-production with [[Star Cinema]]\n|-\n| ''Bekikang: Ang Nanay kong Beki''\n| October 23\n|\n|-\n| ''[[When the Love Is Gone]]''\n| November 27\n|\n|-\n| ''[