ormation with no source will be deleted. Thanks! :)\n\n\u2022 DO NOT RE-EDIT and remove the references/sources and additional information. All information added without references WILL BE DELETED.\n\n\u2022 ADDING REFERENCES \u2013 references should be placed in the notes section if the titled film has a wikipedia article. If the film does not have any link or article page here in Wikipedia, the reference should be indicated in the title of the film section.\n\n\u2022 If adding a film to the roster of upcoming films, PLEASE PLACE IT ACCORDING TO RELEASE DATE, WITH RELIABLE SOURCE/S. Thanks! :)\n\n!!!OTHER IMPORTANT NOTES BEFORE ADDING UPCOMING FILMS IN THE LIST:!!!\n\n1. UNTITLED FILM \u2013 If the film that you are going to place is still untitled but the news/article says the film is in either approved, legit, and is in production, please indicate it as \"Untitled film\".\n\n2. RELEASE DATE OF THE FILM \u2013 only put the release date of the film if it is officially announced by the production company or the news/article you have been put as sourced. If the film release date has not been announced, indicate or put it as \"TBA\" shortened for \"To be announced\".\n\n\u2022 EVERYTHING YOU HAVE BEEN CONTRIBUTED HERE WILL REFLECT TO THE PERSON WHO SEARCHES, VIEWS, VISITS, AND CHECKS THE ARTICLES FROM ALL OVER THE WORLD. IT IS IMPORTANT THAT WE CONTRIBUTE RELIABLY SO THAT WE CAN PROMOTE OUR OWN ENTERTAINMENT INDUSTRY.\n\n\u2022 THIS NOTE IS APPLICABLE TO THE ARTICLES OF FILM PRODUCTION OF THE PHILIPPINES HERE IN WIKIPEDIA\u2013BOTH ENGLISH AND TAGALOG.\n\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\n;Color key\n{{plainlist|\n* {{Color box|#FFFACD|border=darkgray}} \u2013 a foreign film distributed by Viva International Pictures\n* {{Color box|#FFFFFF|border=darkgray}} \u2013 Film(s) that are not colored/white colored are regular release in the cinemas and is not an entry to any film festival inside or outside th