84' stumbles, 'South Park' recovers|website=[[TV By The Numbers]]|language=en|access-date=November 1, 2019|date=October 31, 2019|last=Rejent|first=Joseph}}</ref>\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|30}}\n|ShortSummary = Randy's daughter Shelly has issues with Randy and his marijuana farming. Butters has a problem with a mummy who is very manipulative in their relationship.\n|ProdCode = 2305\n|LineColor = #B9E1FA\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|South Park (season 23)\n|EpisodeNumber = 303\n|EpisodeNumber2 = 6\n|Title = [[Season Finale (South Park)|Season Finale]]\n|DirectedBy = Trey Parker\n|WrittenBy = Trey Parker\n|Viewers = 0.84<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/wednesday-cable-ratings-november-6-2019/|title=Wednesday cable ratings: NBA defeats 'American Horror Story' and 'South Park'|website=[[TV By The Numbers]]|language=en|access-date=November 8, 2019|date=November 7, 2019|last=Rejent|first=Joseph}}</ref>\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|11|6}}\n|ShortSummary = Randy is accused of bombing private marijuana fields, and wants President Garrison to help him defend himself; the White family adopts two kids detained by ICE after the death of their son.\n|ProdCode = 2306\n|LineColor = #B9E1FA\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|South Park (season 23)\n|EpisodeNumber = 304\n|EpisodeNumber2 = 7\n|Title = [[Board Girls]]\n|DirectedBy = Trey Parker\n|WrittenBy = Trey Parker\n|Viewers = 0.85<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/wednesday-cable-ratings-november-13-2019/ |title= Wednesday cable ratings: NBA comes out on top, 'South Park' passes 'American Horror Story' |website=[[TV By The Numbers]]|language=en|access-date=November 14, 2019|date=November 14, 2019|last=Rejent|first=Joseph}}</ref>\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|11|13}}\n|ShortSummary = Strong Woman deals with a transgender athlete who has her own agenda. When the girls want to join a boys' gaming club, the boys object but the girls prove to b