remiereDate\">{{cite web |last1=Nissen |first1=Dano |title=TV News Roundup: Comedy Central Sets 'South Park' Season 23 Premiere Date |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/tv-roundup-south-park-comedy-central-1203272467/ |website=Variety |date=July 18, 2019 |accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref> This season contained the 300th episode of the long-running TV show; the milestone was reached on October 9, 2019, when the third episode of the season premiered. Like previous seasons, this season also had dark weeks (weeks during which no new episode would air), after episodes four and seven. [[Trey Parker]] and [[Matt Stone]] continued to write, direct, and edit every episode the week prior to air, as the duo has done since the series debuted in 1997.<ref name=\"thewrap\" />\n\nSimilar to previous seasons, the season features continuing elements and a recurring storyline, from episodes 1 through 6, without adhering to a linear story arc, while lampooning [[U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement#Detention centers|ICE detention centers]], the 2019 film ''[[Joker (2019 film)|Joker]]'',  media [[censorship in China]], the [[antivaccine movement]], plant based food, the [[Trump Administration]], [[transgenderism]] in athletics, and the competition between traditional [[cable television]] and media streaming.\n\n==Production==\nOn July 8, 2015, two months prior to the season 19 premiere, Comedy Central announced they had renewed ''South Park'' for an additional 30 episodes over three seasons. This renewal was in addition to the two-year contract already in place with Parker and Stone, guaranteeing ''South Park'' would air until at least 2019.<ref name=\"thewrap\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/south-park-scores-3-season-renewal-set-to-top-300-episodes/|title='South Park' Renewed for 3 More Seasons|first=Tony|last=Maglio|website=[[The Wrap]]|date=July 8, 2015|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"deadline\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/07/south-park-renewed-three-seasons-2019-comedy-central-1201472071/|title='South Park' Renewed For Three More Seasons|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|last=Hipes|first=Patrick|date=July 8, 2015|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/south-park-renewed-2019-comedy-central-1201535909/|title='South Park' Renewed by Comedy Central Through 2019|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=July 8, 2015|accessdate=September 5, 2019|last=Steinberg|first=Brian}}</ref> On September 12, 2019, the show was renewed for seasons 24 through 26 until 2022.<ref>{{cite press release|title='South Park' Renewed Through Historic 26th Season|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/09/12/south-park-renewed-through-historic-26th-season-391304/20190912comedycentral01/|website=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=September 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Main theme==\n{{see also|South Park#Main theme}}\nThis season had multiple changes to the traditional [[theme song]] from the show. For the first six episodes of the season, an overall story arc focusing on [[Randy and Sharon Marsh|Randy Marsh]]'s marijuana farm named Tegridy Farms was featured. During these episodes, the theme song's lyrics and graphics were changed to focus on Tegridy Farms and also featured vocals by Randy Marsh and [[Towelie (character)|Towelie]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QQN1l1_Mt7k|title=South Park Gets a New Theme Song Courtesy of Tegridy Farms|website=[[YouTube]]|date=September 26, 2019|accessdate=November 19, 2019}}</ref> In the episode \"[[Board Girls]]\", the regular theme was completely abandoned and replaced with a theme about the PC Babies, the [[politically correct]] children of [[PC Principal]] and Vice Principal [[List of South Park Elementary staff#Strong Woman|Strong Woman]]. In the \"[[Turd Burglars]]\" episode, the theme returned to the show, but starring the women of South Park, in a fictional show titled \"One for the Ladies\". In the \"[[Basic Cable (South Park)|Basic Cable]]\" episode, the theme was abandoned again and replaced with a faux intro titled \"The Scott Malkinson Show\". The traditional theme song was put back in on the final episode \"[[Christmas Snow (South Park)|Christmas Snow]]\".\n\n==Controversy==\nOn October 7, 2019, ''South Park'' was reportedly banned from the Chinese Internet with videos, mentions, and discussion forums for the animated series being removed and shut down in response to episode 2 of the season, \"[[Band in China]]\". Later in the day ''South Park'' creators Trey Parker and Matt Stone mockingly apologized.<ref>{{cite web|title='South Park' creators issue a mocking 'apology' to China after the show was reportedly banned in the country|url=https://www.businessinsider.nl/south-park-creators-issue-mock-apology-to-china-after-ban-2019-10?international=true&r=US|website=[[Business Insider]]|date=October 7, 2019|last=Clark|first=Travis}}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{see also|List of South Park episodes}}\n<onlyinclude>{{Episode table|background=#B9E1FA |overall=|season=|title=|titleR=|airdate=|airdateR=<ref name=\"futon\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/south-park/listings/|title=Shows A\u2013Z \u2013 south park on comedy central|website=[[The Futon Critic]]|accessdate=September 24, 2019}}</ref>|director=|writer=|prodcode=|viewers=  |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|South Park (season 23)\n|EpisodeNumber = 298\n|EpisodeNumber2 = 1\n|Title = [[Mexican Joker]]\n|DirectedBy = [[Trey Parker]]\n|WrittenBy = Trey Parker\n|Viewers = 0.92<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/wednesday-cable-ratings-september-25-2019/|title=Wednesday cable ratings: 'American Horror Story' continues in front, 'South Park' premieres down|website=[[TV by the Numbers]]|accessdate=September 27, 2019|last=Rejent|first=Joseph|date=September 26, 2019}}</ref>\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|9|25}}\n|ShortSummary = When Tegridy Farms' sales dec